Wolves Beats West Brom to Boost Fight Against Premier League Relegation

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-05-08T12:54:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/wolves-beats-west-brom-to-boost-fight-against-premier-league-relegation.html
Wolverhampton Wanderers beat West
Bromwich Albion 3-1 today to climb out of the relegation
positions in English soccer’s Premier League with two rounds of
matches remaining.  Steven Fletcher got two goals at Molineux, with Adlene
Guedioura also scoring for the home team.  Peter Odemwingie 
replied for West Brom with a penalty kick.  Wolves move up two spots to 17th on 37 points, one ahead of
Blackpool and Wigan, with West Ham on 33 points. The bottom
three teams are relegated at the end of the season.  In today’s other matches, Chelsea will move ahead of
 Manchester United  atop the standings if it beats its rival.
Third-place Arsenal is at Stoke.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  